    "body": "> pls search for th duplicate issue of this\r\n\r\nHere are similar issues I found:\r\n- #7001 and (at least judging from your [suggestion](https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/issues/14873#issuecomment-286512473)) #14873 are specific to booleans\r\n- #14423 applies to ``apply``, which in my case works fine\r\n- #14849 applies to ``datetime``\r\n\r\nThe fix might actually the same. As far as I understand, the key lies in your [sentence](https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/issues/14873#issuecomment-266715451) \".groupby tries to cast back to the original types which is generally the correct result.\" - my impression is that we could instead feed the result to ``np.array`` and let it find the appropriate type, regardless of the original type. But then, I still didn't look at the code."
