    "body": "> feed the result to np.array and let it find the appropriate type, regardless of the original type. But then, I \r\n\r\n``np.array`` doesn't do anything. the issue is that we have a computation that works on floats. you *may* have integers as a result, so you *can* try to downcast (IOW and they are equal and no nans), and that is what we do.\r\n\r\nfor the particular case of ``len``, this could simply be intercepted and treated as ``.size()`` (we DO this generally, but maybe not for ``len``, I think we do it for builtin sum)."
